<br>
I was blessed with getting a SEoC a long time ago and my main hand (Earthcaller)...sucks for anything but solo'ing.  I bought a set of claws from a guildmate for 6 k (loan that I'm still paying back) that are 11 18 and some inferior stats than Earthcaller 14 24.  Earthcaller has a 50% slow and a 20 point/6 sec DoT proc.  Personally, I don't think it procs quite often enough, and if there's a shaman or enchanter in the group, I guarantee that that proc won't stick.  (Gets resisted relatively often, to boot).  And the thought of solo'ing makes me want to cry.  I've solo'ed too much, and post 50 ranger solo'ing makes you want to quit.  Too much to kill, with too much risk, a lot of dying, and too little exp rewards.  And early and mid-50 rangers can't seem to find a group for some reason.  (p.s. I do a good 35 dps melee without using spells)<br>
<br>
I've parsed Earthcaller vs. Curved Claws (aforementioned 11 18 1HS).  Right now, the 11 18 that is a drop from Tier 2 does 6% more damage, and is much easier to get than Earthcaller is for most rangers.<br>
<br>
I truly love my epic however, to say I've done it.  I just wish that I had a reason to wield both blades in an exp group.<br>
<br>
Not sure quite how to go about upgrading it.  Thought about making it a 14/20 or 14/21 (any more, and it intrudes on NToV level gear), but the proc in fighting in an area where a slower is REQUIRED, not nice, but REQUIRED like PoP due to mob sheer DPS; and where shaman and enchanters have 70% (enchanter) or a shaman's 75% slow by level 60 which they get at 58, Earthcaller's measly 50% slow just can't compete.  Oh, and Beastlords get a 65% slow spell somewhere, and their epic's slow is 55% and a 460 DoT over 2.3 minutes.  Personally I think someone copied the ranger's epics and tweaked them when they made them.<br>
<br>
Anyways, for the risk vs. time vs. rewards, MOST epic quests are worth it.  Personally, I feel mages get screwed over the most epics vs. PoP, because their epic is a spell to summon a  pet that can go toe to toe with any other pet, even their PoP pets, but doesn't have some abilities needed to compete in PoP, that the 61+ pets get, such as enrage, and the epic pet can't land it's innate procs on PoP encounters because the pet's level is ~46, which make up a large share of the pets DPS.  Mages CAN get around this, with an item from VT.  However, basically when dinging 61, the mage epic pet takes a backseat ride to the 6 and 62 pets.  And say what you will, the magician epic is THE hardest epic to complete due to sheer rare drops from rare spawns, and things to get from rare places, requiring a hellish amount of work.  (Hello 7th Isle PoSky.  Hello PoHate.  Hey Phinigel Autotropos)<br>
<br>
However, Sony would likely sooner return FV to it's original ruleset than change the epics for the better (hey, nerfs can always happen).  The hastle of coding new mobs to give out quests on the level of epic quests for the amount of turn-ins, quest talk, and the like makes for an ungodly amount of programming, bugging, and debugging, not to mention as someone said, the sheer class envy and KS'ing that comes about from the epic quests makes for a CS nightmare.<br>
<br>
So, likely, if you wanted to see an epic quest for your class to come about, I'd start by making a REASONABLE reward, probably something on the level between Tier 4 and Tier 5 (the 4 elemental planes and PoTime).  (No, I haven't a clue about what's appropriate per class for anything other than ranger gear, with a small inkling of mage gear thrown in).  Then, figure out a REASONABLE list of spawns to kill, with a somewhat REASONABLE drop rate (don't make it a 1 in 2000 drop rate from something like a prisoner in PoJ, and don't make it a 1 in 3 drop from Corinav, the Avatar of Water, unless it was say the final piece).  You WILL need some sort of bottleneck, probably even 2 or 3.  These would be drops from your rare and hard to kill stuff (gods, planar bosses, etc.)  (For rangers it used to be VS remains, and the PoSky.  Also the SEoC for Earthcaller, but many, many rangers skipped Earthcaller)  Then you work it all into a storyline, preferably a storyline that can go well with the entire theme of PoP.<br>
<br>
Can't think of anything else to say.  I know it's a long post. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=roninsenshi>RoninSenshi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senshi No Adakia<br>Jihad on that ass!</span><br>  Posts: 2054<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/5/03 2:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3611.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/sageofthehalo/Shintou.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Well damnit</span><hr size=1> I'm just lucky I guess, if the Hide rate has not changed..<br>
